Program: Omnibus
Title: Flight from Love
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376jks
Last Broadcast Date: 31 January 1989
A look at the record-breaking journey made by the American Voyager aircraft, the first plane to fly around the world without refueling. Pilots Dick Rutan and Jeana Yeager talk about their doomed love affair, while brother and aerospace engineer Burt Rutan talks about the romance of flight.